About this hotel

This refined guesthouse in a traditional riad is an 8-minute walk from the bustling Jemaa el-Fnaa public square and 4 km from the tranquil Majorelle Garden.

Check-in time: 2:00 PM
Check-out time: 12:00 PM

    Classic Moroccan Riad/guesthouse/hotel. Quite traditional in the old town part of Marrakech. Can seem intimidating arriving there but go with it and you will be rewarded with a memorable stay.

    There is a lovely roof terrace with a quite small pool and a separate hot tub jacuzzi.

    Riad Zitoun Jdid

    Charming Riad Zitoun Jdid has a number of bistros with rooftop terraces, serving mint tea and European food with Moroccan twists. Riad hotels, in grand former homes with inner courtyards, sit alongside traditional hammams and shops selling pottery, kaftans and leather bags. The 19th-century Bahia Palace has intricately decorated interiors and walled gardens, while Dar Si Siad Museum shows crafts and Berber jewelry.

    About this hotel

    This refined guesthouse in a traditional riad is an 8-minute walk from the bustling Jemaa el-Fnaa public square and 4 km from the tranquil Majorelle Garden. …

    The 7 elegant rooms have free Wi-Fi, satellite TV and safes, as well as en suite bathrooms; some feature carved-wood doors, ornate wood furnishings and/or stained-glass windows. Room service is available 24/7.

    Complimentary amenities include all-day mint tea, plus breakfast served in-room, or on a terrace that has panoramic city views; evening meals can be arranged. There's also an airy courtyard lounge with a fireplace.
